title: Excavator driver rams car in bid to stop Melbourne police chase - 9news.com.au
text:
Excavator driver rams car in bid to stop Melbourne police chase By 9NEWS The dumped Barina (right) after it caused havoc on Melbourne roads. (9NEWS) 
A quick-thinking excavator driver is being praised for trying to help police stop a car diving wildly through Melbourne’s south-east this morning. 
Chris, an excavator driver, told 3AW he saw the white Holden Barina being chased by police just after 6am in Berwick. 
“I clipped the back of him, spun him around, then I was up next to him and I could’ve got him but I didn’t know where to push him,” he said. 
“He’s gone up on someone’s front lawn and taken off.” 
The car was eventually dumped about 6.30am in Maramba Drive in Narre Warren. 
A number of items have been seized from the car beaten-up car including power tools and bolt cutters. 
Witnesses reported seeing the white car speed and allegedly ram other cars along the Monash Freeway and in Belgrave, Boronia and Berwick. 
One person was arrested, however the other two occupants of the car fled the scene. 
It’s believed those on the run are teenagers. 
Anyone with information is urged to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000. © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
